      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "As I was writing some docs,I realized that GetTime is always called, even when `nMaxOutboundLimit` is zero (i.e. no ` -maxuploadtarget` is set)\r\n\r\nShouldn't the [code](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/src/net.cpp#L2858) look like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\n    if (nMaxOutboundLimit) {\r\n        const auto now = GetTime<std::chrono::seconds>();\r\n        if (nMaxOutboundCycleStartTime + MAX_UPLOAD_TIMEFRAME < now)\r\n        {\r\n            // timeframe expired, reset cycle\r\n            nMaxOutboundCycleStartTime = now;\r\n            nMaxOutboundTotalBytesSentInCycle = 0;\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n```\r\nOr should we call [GetMaxOutboundTarget](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/src/net.cpp#L2875) ? There's a lock in that method. Maybe that's too expensive of a call?\r\n",
      "created_at" : "2021-09-29T12:44:54Z",
      "html_url" : "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/23128#issuecomment-930140654",
      "id" : 930140654,
